@title UserContract
 @dev This contract work as a centralized user's system, where all users has your userType here

@dev Returns the user type if the user is registered
 @param addr the user address that want check if exists
@dev Returns the enum UserType of the system
@dev Modifier to check if user type is UNDEFINED when register

devdoc.details: This contract work as a centralized user's system, where all users has your userType here

addUser(address,uint8).details: Add new user in the system

params.userType: The type of the user - enum UserType

getUser(address).details: Returns the user type if the user is registered

params.addr: the user address that want check if exists

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

userTypes().details: Returns the enum UserType of the system

devdoc.title: UserContract
